class Solution {
public:
    int missingNumber(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int add = (n*(n+1))/2;
        int sum = 0;
        int missing_no = 0;
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            sum+=nums[i];
        }
        missing_no = add-sum;
        return missing_no;
    }
};

"idea:
This approach finds the missing number using the sum formula of first n natural numbers.
Since the array contains numbers from 0 to n with one number missing, the expected total sum is calculated using:
n(n+1)/2
The variable add stores this expected sum, while sum stores the actual sum of elements present in the array.
A loop traverses the array and adds every element to sum.
The missing number is obtained by subtracting the actual sum from the expected sum (add - sum).
Finally, the result is returned as the missing element in the range.
"

#Time Complexity: O(n)                                                                    Space Complexity: O(1)
